Interface PersistOperation

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseFileListEditCommand, BaseKickstartCommand, BaseKickstartScriptCommand, BasePersistOperation, BaseSystemOperation, BaseTreeEditOperation, BaseUpdateChannelCommand, CancelKickstartSessionOperation, CreateFileListCommand, EditFileListCommand, FilePreservationListsCommand, KickstartActivationKeysCommand, KickstartCloneCommand, KickstartCryptoKeyCommand, KickstartDeleteCommand, KickstartEditCommand, KickstartEditPackagesCommand, KickstartFileDownloadCommand, KickstartIpCommand, KickstartLocaleCommand, KickstartOptionsCommand, KickstartPackageProfileCommand, KickstartPartitionCommand, KickstartScheduleCommand, KickstartScriptCreateCommand, KickstartScriptDeleteCommand, KickstartScriptEditCommand, KickstartTroubleshootingCommand, ProvisionVirtualInstanceCommand, SystemDetailsCommand, TreeCreateOperation, TreeDeleteOperation, TreeEditOperation, UpdateBaseChannelCommand, UpdateChildChannelsCommand

    public interface PersistOperation
    PersistOperation - interface defining a way to store objects to a persistence layer. The main method is "store()" that defines the Operation for storing an Object to the db.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      User getUser()
      All PersistOperations must have a User object who is performing the Operation.
      ValidatorError store()
      Perform the storage Operation to the Persistence Layer.
